# PHASE 3  - LIVE ALERTS
Use two modes, not one.

Best approach
Mode	How it works	Use case
Auto-refresh polling	Fetch LTP every 1–5 mins	Portfolio dashboard MVP
WebSocket streaming	Live tick feed from Kite	Trading / near real-time alerts

For your dashboard, start with polling. Kite’s REST quote/LTP APIs support fetching LTP/quotes for many instruments in one request, while WebSocket is meant for live streaming using instrument tokens.

Option 1: Polling MVP

Install:

uv add streamlit-autorefresh

Use:

from streamlit_autorefresh import st_autorefresh

### REFRESH every 2 minutes
st_autorefresh(interval=120_000, key="ltp_refresh")

Then fetch only LTP:

def fetch_live_ltp(kite, symbols):
    instruments = [f"NSE:{s}" for s in symbols]
    data = kite.ltp(instruments)

    rows = []
    for key, value in data.items():
        symbol = key.split(":")[1]
        rows.append({
            "Symbol": symbol,
            "LTP": value["last_price"]
        })

    return pd.DataFrame(rows)

Merge with dashboard data:

ltp_df = fetch_live_ltp(kite, symbols)

dashboard_df = dashboard_df.drop(columns=["LTP"], errors="ignore")
dashboard_df = dashboard_df.merge(ltp_df, on="Symbol", how="left")
Recommended flow
App starts
↓
Load holdings from Supabase
↓
Load historical metrics from Supabase/cache
↓
Every 2 mins:
    fetch only LTP from Kite
    update Streamlit session_state
    recompute:
        P&L
        EMA distance
        range position
        alerts
↓
Render dashboard

Do not refetch historical data every 2 minutes.

Option 2: WebSocket live feed

Use only if you need true live ticks.

Kite WebSocket
↓
Background listener
↓
Store latest LTP in memory/Supabase
↓
Streamlit reads latest prices

Problem:

Streamlit reruns often
WebSocket should not restart on every rerun
Better to run WebSocket as a separate worker process

Recommended structure:

streamlit_app.py
workers/kite_ws_worker.py
supabase

The worker writes latest prices to Supabase:

live_prices
- symbol
- instrument_token
- ltp
- updated_at

Streamlit reads from Supabase every 1–2 minutes.

Practical recommendation

For your current stage:

Button click fetch → replace with 2-min polling

Later:

2-min polling → separate WebSocket worker

Use WebSocket only when:

you need intraday tick charts
instant price alerts
live trading signals
very fast LTP updates

For portfolio review, 2-minute polling is enough.